Usage : 
  ./lockfile
    -c : check lockfile
         Will be Kill the calling process, when the lock file exists
          and proccess id is alive to lock file written.
         if lockfile check is ok, create lock file and write to the id of calling proccess.
    -r : remove lockfile
    -f : specify the lock file name.
          Default is '/tmp/.{command of calling proccess}.lock'.
